FBIS3-36026 "drsov022_b_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-022 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Feb 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Report Says Half of Armed Forces Combat Ready MK0102143094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 30 Jan 94 p 1 MK0102143094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Russian Army Only Half Ready for Combat"] [Text] MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS has learned information from reliable sources about the state of the Russian Federation Armed Forces' combat readiness. According to classified documents of the Russian Federation Defense Ministry, only 51 percent of Armed Forces personnel are capable of performing combat missions. Only one division in every military district is capable of taking part in combat operations, the Inspectorate for the Russian Federation Armed Forces' Combat Readiness reports. Only 20 percent of tanks in service can be considered combat ready. As for naval requirements -- putting a ship on full alert within 45 minutes -- only a few ships of the Russian Navy are able to fulfill them.
